This all boils down to what the real ZEM nerf is. <br>
<br>
If its high as Velael says, 44% instead of 70%, a 37% decrease in xp per kill, then the group modifier is simply not going to cut it.<br>
<br>
SoE says the group bonus will range from 20-80% which supposedly could break down as 2 people 20% 3 people 40% 4 people 60% 5 people 80%.<br>
<br>
Using Velael's 37% nerf, you woul dneed to be in a 3 person group to break even, and this patch would help you if you are usually in groups of 4 or more people in PoP. <br>
<br>
however, according to SoE:<br>
<br>
[/quote]Accordingly, the bonus inherent to Planes of Power zones will be decreased slightly. However, as long as person is grouped with at least one other, they will see an improvement in experience gain over the old system. [/quote]<br>
<br>
If Velael is right, then they have already lied to us about this, and its easy to imagine them lying about the amount of bonus as well. We should have more people test this and check for the ZEM Decline in PoP zones with this patch before we really panic about it, so we are working on better knowledge.<br>
<br>
