<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>There are people out there, whether you choose to believe it or not, who have trouble getting groups, and havent done anything wrong other than had the poor taste to be closer to lvl 61 than lvl 65. They have friends and such. I just have noticed that as I got closer to 65 people become more interested in groupiong with me. At lower levels I was pretty much forced to solo with my LFG flag up for hours, and these are the people who will suffer.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
When they open up experience to other zones, there should be less pressure to go for AA before leveling because of lack of areas to exp.  Opening up zones will also help with this. If after these changes certain classes are found less desirable in grouping environment, then they should be looked at.  By opening up older world zones, perhaps even porting will be more desirable.  Okay, maybe that is a bit of a stretch.<br>
<br>
Solo experience should probably be only equal or possibly marginally better than group experience to account for the fact that you are less likely to get significant equipment upgrade, and that death while soloing usually will lead to greater downtime.<br>
<br>
As far as PoP zones having high ZEMs, I think this was a mistake.  Power gained by moving up should be incremental not exponential.  This should be true for equipment, AA, and levels.  With big jumps in power, EQ would have a hard time out-doing the previous expansion(s) without messing up balance.  Players now are learning to expect big jumps in power.  I would personally like to see EQ1 last for a long time.  I am guessing that at some point in the future it will be necessary to increase the level cap again just to give higher end players goals and equipment to keep the game fun.<br>
<br>
Gwideon<br>
PHENOMENAL COSMIC POWER!<br>
in an itty bitty living space<br>
