<br>
as for the nerf to solo xp. you can argue about the specifics all you want. but it looks clear to me they are intent on nerfing it, that solo xp is more productive than soe intended. i dont think they want people getting a hundred aa's in just a couple weeks. and i'm talking normal people, not full time gamers with no life.  the only thing that slows down aa progression currently is raiding. as that takes away time you'd normally spend getting aa's.<br>
<br>
and no offence but soloing for xp should not yeild more xp per hour than any 6 man group (unless said group has no idea what they are doing).  at the very least the two should be equal.  but in many cases, they are not.<br>
<br>
like one of the above posters said. many group only classes wont even bother looking for groups if they have less than 2 hours. it's not worth it. it's rude to look for a group only to tell them 30 minutes later you have to leave in 30 minutes.  that may not sound like alot. but once you add it up there's a huge descrepency over time.  look at weekdays. say you get home at 5:30. your guild starts raiding at 6:30.  that's an hour of nothing to do as a group only class. as a solo class that's an hour of xp. over the course of a week that's 5 or more aa's. i dare you to look me in the eye and tell me that's fair.<br>
<br>
so how is current soloing balanced when it can be done with shorts amount of free time and gains more xp?  so forgive me if i dont cry a river for those people that only solo. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimstafftheurgist>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 8060<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 10:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: </span><hr size=1> I like how it is.  These look like good changes to me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seriati>Seriati</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 400<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 11:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE: hmmm</span><hr size=1> On the example provided with respect to a 1000 XP mob in a zone with a ZEM of 35%.  Could someone confirm that 650XP (apparently calculated 1000XP -35%) post patch is an incorrect number.  A 1000 XP mob currently, should give about 741 XP post fix (741 +35% ZEM = 1000).  <br>
<br>
That being the case, pre-correction a 2 person group killing said mob each got 510 XP (1000XP + 2% group modifier / 2).  And now they will get about 445 XP (741 + 20% / 2), which means they'll have lost about 13% of the XP.  Of course this presumes that the ZEM will drop from 35% to 0%.  The soloer should lose about 26% of the experience per kill.<br>
<br>
The duoing group will also be substantially better off in any zone that does not have such a high ZEM modifier than they would before, because they will each get 600 XP - rather than 510XP per 1000 XP kill.<br>
<br>
Giving that grouping seemed to be a penalty at times, I think on the whole these changes should be good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yyidth>yyidth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 297<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 11:07 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmmm</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>That being said, I'm off to a damn 4 hour budget meeting, 10x less fun than even xp'ing in PoP!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
